{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}COMPONENT SETTINGS{% endblock %}

{% block body %}

    <div class="termsAndConditionsOfPayementContainer">
        <div class="title">
            <h3>Terms and Conditions</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="body">

            <div class="section">
                <span>Late Payment Consequences</span>
                <p>In the event of a late payment, project delivery may be delayed, potentially extending beyond the originally agreed deadline.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Dispute Resolution</span>
                <p>In case of disagreement, parties will attempt to resolve the issue amicably through discussion and negotiation. If unresolved, parties may choose to engage a neutral mediator or arbitrator to assist in resolving the dispute.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Project Cancellation</span>
                <ul>
                    <li>Full Refund: If the project is canceled before work begins, a full refund may be issued.</li>
                    <li>Partial Refund: If the project is canceled after work has started, a partial refund reflecting the work completed may be considered.</li>
                    <li>No Refund: No refund may be provided if a significant portion of the project has been completed.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Non-Payment</span>
                <p>In case of non-payment, no penalty fees will be charged, but services will be suspended until payment is received.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Confidentiality Agreements</span>
                <p>Both parties agree to maintain confidentiality of all proprietary and sensitive information disclosed during the project. This agreement remains in effect even after the project is completed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Contract Termination Conditions</span>
                <p>Breach of Contract: The contract may be terminated if either party fails to meet its obligations, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Non-payment by the client.</li>
                    <li>Failure to deliver services by the provider as agreed upon.</li>
                    <li>Breach of confidentiality agreements.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Mutual Agreement: The contract can be terminated at any time if both parties agree.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="section">
                <span>Payment Milestones</span>
                <ul>
                    <li>Initial Deposit: A percentage of the total cost paid upfront to initiate the project.</li>
                    <li>Progress Payments: Payments made at specific stages of project completion (e.g., 25%, 50%, and 75% completion).</li>
                    <li>Final Payment: The remaining balance is due upon project completion and client approval.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>


        </div>
    </div>

{% endblock %}